Earlier computed conditional probability\[
\mbox{P(Type O | Female)} = \frac{202}{430} 
\]numerator 202 came count Females blood Type B, denominator 430 total number Females.
divide numerator denominator 1000, quotient changed, \[
\mbox{P(Type O | Female)} = \frac{202/1000}{430/1000} 
= \frac{0.202}{0.43} = \frac{\mbox{P(Type O Female)}}{\mbox{P(Female)}}
\]illustrates general property probability: B represent possible outcomes, probability given B \[
\mbox{P(| B)} = \frac{\mbox{P(B)}}{\mbox{P(B)}}
\]Multiplying sides equation P(B) gives\[
\mbox{P(B)} = \mbox{P(| B)}\mbox{P(B)}  
\]called multiplication rule. Reversing order B gives\[
\mbox{P(B )} = \mbox{P(B | )}\mbox{P()}  
\]blood type example, clear P(Female Type O) P(Type O Female).
true general: P(B) = P(B )}, follows 
\[
\mbox{Pr($|$ B)}\mbox{Pr(B)}  = \mbox{Pr(B $|$ )}\mbox{Pr()} 
\]

\[
\mbox{Pr($|$ B)}  = \mbox{Pr(B $|$ )}\frac{\mbox{Pr()}}{\mbox{Pr(B)}}
\]
